ProtoTheorem:
. "Let $D$ be a UFD and $F$ its field of fractions. If $p(x)$ 
   is a monic polynomial in $D $ with $p(x) = f(x) g(x)$ in $F 
   $, then $p(x) = f_1(x) g_1(x)$, where $f_1(x)$ and $g_1(x)$ 
   are in $D $. Furthermore, $\deg f(x) = \deg f_1(x)$ and 
   $\deg g(x) = \deg g_1(x)$."
